  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can apply for residency certificate in India?",
  "response": "Applying for a residency certificate in India typically involves submitting several documents to prove your residency. The process may vary slightly depending on the specific state or union territory you live in, as local governments may have different requirements.\n\nHere is a general outline of the steps you may follow to obtain a residency certificate:\n\n### 1. Gather Required Documents\n\n1. **Proof of Residence:** This could be any of the following:\n    - Rental agreement or lease deed\n    - Recent utility bills (electricity, water, gas)\n    - Property tax receipt\n    - Bank or post office passbook\n2. **Identity Proof:** Such as:\n    - Aadhaar card\n    - PAN card\n    - Voter ID card\n    - Passport\n3. **Application Form:** Obtain the specific application form for a residency certificate from your local municipal or district office or their official website.\n\n### 2. Fill in the Application Form\n\n- Complete the application form with accurate details of your name, date of birth, address, etc.\n- Attach the required documents listed above.\n\n### 3. Submit the Application\n\n- Submit the completed application form along with the necessary supporting documents to the designated government office or online portal.\n- Pay any applicable fee for processing the application.\n\n### 4. Verification\n\n- The authorities will conduct a verification process which may include a physical visit to your residence.\n- They may check the submitted documents for authenticity.\n\n### 5. Collect Your Residency Certificate\n\n- Once your application is approved, you will be notified.\n- You can collect your residency certificate from the office where you submitted the application or it may be sent to your residence by post.\n\n### State-Specific Guidelines\n\n- Visit the official website or office of your state or union territory\u2019s revenue or municipal department for detailed instructions that are specific to your location.\n- Some states offer online application facilities for convenience.\n\n### Online Application (If Available)\n\nIf your state/UT offers an online application process, follow these steps:\n\n1. Visit the official e-governance portal of your state.\n2. Register or log in.\n3. Fill in the online application form.\n4. Upload scanned copies of required documents.\n5. Submit the form and pay any applicable fees online.\n6. Track the status online.\n7. Download or print the residency certificate once approved.\n\n### Contact Local Authorities\n\n- For specific guidance, visit your local municipal office or contact the local revenue department.\n- They can provide you with the latest updates and detailed instructions.\n\nRemember, the procedures and requirements might change, so verifying the latest information from local authorities is crucial.",
